thread.title: Former Nicholls State, Alabama RB Altee Tenpenny dies in car wreck, AL.com reports
thread.title_full: Former Nicholls State, Alabama RB Altee Tenpenny dies in car wreck, AL.com reports | NOLA.com

author: Jim Kleinpeter, NOLA.com | The Times-Picayune
title: Former Nicholls State, Alabama RB Altee Tenpenny dies in car wreck, AL.com reports
text:
Altee Tenpenny, a former Nicholls State and Alabama running back, was killed in a one-car accident in Mississippi Tuesday evening, AL.com reported.
Tenpenny collided with a highway sign on Mississippi Highway 1 about 5 p.m., according to the Mississippi Highway Patrol. He was traveling back home to Arkansas after being dimissed from the Nicholls State football team following his arrest Sunday morning for possession of a firearm and discharging a weapon .
Tenpenny was one of the top rated running backs in the nation out of North Little Rock High School but left Alabama in January and transferred to UNLV. He was dismissed from that team in August before going to Nicholls State.
